  <title>Using Objects and Methods</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>
      This unit introduces the Java programming language and the use of
      variables and classes. Students will learn about three built-in data types
      and how to create variables, store values, and interact with those
      variables using basic operations and writing arithmetic expressions.
      Students also learn to use Math and String class methods and using objects
      like Turtles and their methods to draw on the screen.
    </p>

